list.item:
Would allow U.S. to proceed with all
                        ongoing offensive programs, but stops Soviet buildup in offensive
                        launchers;

Would permit MIRV’s and other missile
                        improvements leading to possible future counterforce threat to Minutemen,
                        depending on the agreed levels of ABM’s;

The responses to MIRV’s would probably
                        lead to a continuing qualitative arms competition within the constraints of
                        the agreement;

Assuming the Soviets want a MIRV ban,
                        would make them more willing to accept the other limitations
                        proposed;

MIRV ban would reduce freedom to hedge
against Soviet cheating by restricting U.S.
capabilities to penetrate ABM’s;

Would prevent attainment of U.S.
                        capabilities to cover all Soviet time-urgent nuclear-threat targets which
                        threaten the U.S. and our NATO allies;
